President Trump spoke to reporters before his trip to Pennsylvania, expressing his desire for the state to reopen and praising his administration's response to the pandemic. Press Secretary Kayleigh McEnany discussed the administration's pandemic preparedness efforts and criticized the Obama-Biden plan. Secretary Alex Azar defended the administration's actions and criticized Dr. Bright, who was testifying about the pandemic response. President Trump also defended the use of hydroxychloroquine and criticized Dr. Bright as a disgruntled employee. The President expressed surprise at Senator Burr temporarily stepping down as chairman and denied discussing the investigation into Burr with the Justice Department. He mentioned the possibility of cutting relations with China and expressed dissatisfaction with the World Trade Organization. The President also addressed the CDC's death counts and the administration's testing efforts.